  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel and slice the carrot into 5cm chunks. Slice three pieces of ginger to thickness of a pound and reserve the rest. Chop the spring onions whites, reserving the green tops. Remove and reserve the stems of the shiitake mushrooms."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Put the washed rice, sliced ginger, spring onion whites, carrot chunks, shiitake and the stems, sesame oil, white pepper and a pinch of salt into a medium-sized saucepan. Add the lesser amount of the stock for a thicker consistency or add the full amount for a looser consistency (you can always add more liquid later if you’re not sure). Bring to the boil, add a lid and cook for 15 mins over a low heat, stirring halfway through to check nothing is sticking to the bottom."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, slice one piece of ginger and finely shred. Finely slice the green spring onion tops. Combine the rice sauce ingredients in a small bowl and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "After 15 mins, remove all the aromatics and veggies into a bowl. Use a whisk to vigorously whisk the stock and rice mix for 2 mins, to break up the rice grains. Add the veg back to the pan, plus the cherry tomatoes, and boil with the lid on for 3-5 mins to make creamy. Add more water to make it soupier, if you like – just make sure to bring it to the boil again. Taste and add a little salt if necessary, but remember the rice sauce is also salty."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve with ginger shreds, sliced spring onion tops, the rice sauce, crispy shallots and chilli oil."
    }
  ],
